{
  "texts": [
    "KCNet deeply mines local geometric information through the kernel correlation layer, and combines it with the graph pooling layer to improve the generalization ability of complex scenes.",
    "It has achieved significant performance improvements in multiple tasks such as point cloud classification and semantic segmentation.",
    "For real-time estimation of hand and object poses in 2D and 3D, (Doosti et al. 2020) proposed HOPE-Net using adaptive graph convolutional neural network (AGCN) and graph pooling method.",
    "By reducing the graph size through graph pooling, HOPE-Net successfully captures the local features of hands and objects while maintaining real-time performance, which improves the performance of hand-object pose estimation.",
    "For the 2D to 3D human pose estimation task, (Xu and Takano 2021) proposed a novel graph convolutional network architecture-graph stacked hourglass network."
  ]
}